## Instructions

Analyze the current page state and determine the next action from the test plan. 

1. If no navigation has occurred, start with the first navigation step
2. After each action, take a snapshot of the page to get updated DOM context
3. Verify the action succeeded by checking the DOM
4. Proceed to the next step in the test plan

## Output Format

Return a JSON object with your decision:
```json
{
  "action": "navigate|click|fill|select_option|check|uncheck|hover|dblclick|drag_and_drop|wait|evaluate|assert_text|assert_visible|screenshot|go_back|go_forward|reload|complete",
  "selector": "CSS selector or XPath (if needed)",
  "value": "Value to fill or select (if needed)",
  "url": "URL to navigate to (if action is navigate)",
  "expected": "Expected text for assertions (if action is assert_text)",
  "description": "Description of the action",
  "wait_after": 1000,
  "tool_calls": [
    {
      "name": "browser_navigate|browser_click|browser_fill_form|...",
      "args": {
        "url": "...",
        "fields": [...],
        "value": "..."
      }
    }
  ],
  "has_tool_calls": true,
  "test_complete": false
}
```

**Important**: Set `has_tool_calls` to `true` if you have tool_calls to execute, `false` otherwise. Set `test_complete` to `true` when all test steps are done.

## Important Notes

- ALWAYS use `browser_snapshot` after navigation/interaction to update `last_dom_context`
- Use CSS selectors or XPath for element targeting
- Include `wait_after` milliseconds to allow page to settle
- For assertions, verify the element exists and has expected content
- If an action fails, try alternative selectors or add wait steps
- When all test steps are complete, return `action: "complete"`

## Available Browser Tools

- `browser_navigate(url)` - Navigate to a URL
- `browser_click(selector)` - Click an element using CSS selector or XPath
- `browser_fill_form(fields)` - Fill multiple form fields
- `browser_type(selector, text)` - Type text into an input field
- `browser_hover(selector)` - Hover over an element
- `browser_evaluate(script)` - Execute JavaScript
- `browser_take_screenshot(path)` - Take a screenshot
- `browser_snapshot()` - Capture page snapshot with accessibility tree
- `browser_wait_for(selector, timeout)` - Wait for element to appear
- `browser_press_key(key)` - Press a keyboard key
- `browser_navigate_back()` - Navigate back

Return your next action as a JSON object.